&lt;h3&gt;These hands-on, online sessions are brief kickstarts to moving you from a security mindset (&amp;quot;EVERYONE IS OUT TO GET ME&amp;quot;) to a privacy mindset (&amp;quot;I have a right to privacy for myself and my personal data.&amp;quot;).&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Come to all the sessions or pick a single topic that will improve your data life.&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;em&gt;Bring your device, close some tabs, and be open to improving your digital privacy with a few simple steps and tools. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;// topics //&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;session 1 (02.14): who/what&amp;#39;s a threat to my data?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;session 2 (02.21): finally change your password from 12345&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;session 3 (02.28): options when using (leaky) public wifi&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;session 4 (tbd): mind your business in that browser&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;session 5 (tbd): avoiding malware + viruses&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
