&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The &lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Naomi Prawer Kadar Annual Memorial Lecture&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; provides an opportunity for the public to explore topics of Yiddish language and linguistics, the history of Yiddish, Yiddish children&amp;rsquo;s literature and education. The lecture is supported by the &lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Naomi Prawer Kadar Foundation, Inc.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;, which is dedicated to reimagining education. The Naomi Foundation champions Yiddish, Naomi&amp;rsquo;s lifelong passion, as a vibrant, rich, and contemporary language. The Naomi Foundation advances the teaching and learning of Yiddish, particularly in academic and scholarly settings.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

