&lt;p&gt;In protest of Israel&amp;rsquo;s war on Gaza, students across Western campuses built encampments and called to end the role of their own universities in Palestinian unfreedom. This student movement instigated renewed debates about the imbrication of higher education with imperial violence. Among the student demands, the call to sever ties with Israeli universities sparked considerable institutional opposition. Western university administrators consistently refused to engage the demand, while their Israeli counterparts staged repeated interventions to intercept it. This talk reads the negotiation processes between student organizers and administrators to interrogate how university complicity in violence is constituted as unspeakable. Tracing colonial entanglements across Israeli, European, and North American universities, this talk will show how academic bureaucracy and discourse form an epistemic counterinsurgency against the movement for Palestinian liberation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speaker&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.mayaywind.com/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Maya Wind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a President&amp;rsquo;s and Andrew W. Mellon Postdoctoral Fellow at the University of California, Riverside. Her scholarship explores how settler societies and global systems of militarism and policing are sustained, with a particular focus on the reproduction and export of Israeli security expertise. Her first book,&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Towers of Ivory and Steel: How Israeli Universities Deny Palestinian Freedom&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;(Verso 2024), investigates the complicity of Israeli universities in settler colonialism and apartheid, and her writing on the imbrication of the university with violence have appeared in public and academic journals including&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Cultural Anthropology&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;South Atlantic Quarterly&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Moderated by SOF Fellow&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://sofheyman.org/persons/iheb-guermazi" target="_blank"&gt;Iheb Guermazi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
