&lt;h2&gt;Are you interested in using the cloud to run research analyses but aren&amp;#39;t quite sure how to get started? or are you familiar with AWS but want to explore GCP?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join &lt;a href="https://www.cuit.columbia.edu/rcs" target="_blank"&gt;CUIT Research Computing Services&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;for a session led by Columbia&amp;#39;s Google Cloud Platform (GCP) liasions. This session is designed to introduce researchers at Columbia to the fundamentals of research in the cloud. We aim to cover:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to create a Columbia-linked GCP account (and the benefits of doing so)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Credits available to researchers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;GCP analogs to AWS modules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to set up an instance (server) in the cloud for data analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to run a job / scripts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to access LionMail Drive data in GCP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to store data in the cloud&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to estimate and monitor expenses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have specific topics you&amp;#39;d like to suggest to include, please note them in your registration or email rcs@columbia.edu.&lt;/p&gt;

